    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a pot over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Squeeze your <strong>sausage meat</strong> from the skins into the pan (clean hands is the best way!) and discard the skins</p><p>Break the <strong>sausage meat</strong> up into large bite-sized pieces with a wooden spoon and cook for 5 min or until browned</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-style-coddle-sausage-and-sweet-potato-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sausage meat is cooking, peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s] </strong>in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and chop into chunks</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs</p><p>Once browned, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong>, <strong>carrot discs </strong>and <strong>chopped leek </strong>to the pan and cook for a further 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-style-coddle-sausage-and-sweet-potato-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the veg is softening, cut your <strong>potato[es] </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the veg is beginning to soften, add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-style-coddle-sausage-and-sweet-potato-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and discard the stems</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-style-coddle-sausage-and-sweet-potato-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chicken stock </strong>to the pot with the <strong>thyme leaves</strong>, your <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for 15-20 min or until the veg is tender and the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> Irish-style coddle sausage & potato stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-style-coddle-sausage-and-sweet-potato-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the stew is cooking, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-style-coddle-sausage-and-sweet-potato-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until toasted and crispy</p><p>Once toasted, spread a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> over the <strong>toasted ciabatta</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy buttered ciabatta</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-style-coddle-sausage-and-sweet-potato-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Irish-style coddle sausage & potato stew</strong> with the <strong>crispy buttered ciabatta </strong>to the side and discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
